help 2018-10-10 22:38:45 uhh
help 2018-10-10 22:38:53 i would not recommend pistons for doors
help 2018-10-10 22:39:01 motors are less glitchy
help 2018-10-10 22:39:22 and you need more pistons to push more than 1.5 blocks
help 2018-10-10 22:39:41 use motors like they are hinges
help 2018-10-10 22:41:03 attach the darker side to the frame of the door
help 2018-10-10 22:41:20 and the lighter side should be pointing either upwards or downwards
help 2018-10-10 22:41:44 darker side should only touch the frame by its sides,
help 2018-10-10 22:42:04 not having the full 1x1 dark part touching it
help 2018-10-10 22:42:16 this is harder to tell you without pictures
help 2018-10-10 22:46:07 yes, now make sure there is a block next to that motor which will connect the motor to the frame
help 2018-10-10 22:46:18 and make sure the door doesn't connect with the frame
help 2018-10-10 22:46:28 so i would suggest using wedges and corner wedges
help 2018-10-10 22:47:07 like, using the angled side of a wedge facing towards the door in order to make the door not connect with the door frame and thus not allowing the door to work at all
help 2018-10-11 04:17:47 toby
help 2018-10-11 04:17:54 imagine it like it's a scale
help 2018-10-11 04:18:11 if both balls are too far apart, it'll be impossible to fly
help 2018-10-11 04:18:27 actually no that's not the right metaphor
help 2018-10-11 04:18:46 but what i mean is, if both balls are too far apart, there's no chance it will fly
help 2018-10-11 04:19:06 if your center of mass is up front, and your center of lift is behind it, then the nose will drop
help 2018-10-11 04:19:29 if the mass is at the back, the plane will be back heavy, and it will go up when you aren't using your control surfaces
help 2018-10-11 04:19:40 as in when it's cruising in the air
help 2018-10-11 04:19:55 if your center of mass and lift are close enough together, your plane will fly
help 2018-10-11 04:20:33 but just make sure that wherever those two meet, it's closer to the middle of the plane rather than the front or back, which will compromise its flying effectiveness a lot
help 2018-10-11 04:21:08 so you either need to put more wings closer to the front, or more weight at the back/less weight at the front

contest-info 2019-03-30 01:29:07 A new type of contest has been introduced to this server: **Competitions!**

Instead of contests, where you have a limit of 7 days to complete a creation (or submit an existing one), competitions have a 10 minute timer, and all competitors must stay in the same server in order to be judged after they have all finished their creations. **You do not submit creations for competitions, all creations must be completely built from scratch within the time constraints and on the same server as all other competitors.** This way, it is easier to prove one's skill at this game. There can be multiple competitions ongoing on different servers, and it doesn't matter if there is a contest in progress or not, competitions will have no effect on contests. 

**This does not mean that contests are going to stop anytime soon. We are just introducing a new, more competitive and engaging form of the current contests, as they were meant to be.**

We will use the *secret* community VIP server for hosting competitions. I will give the invite link to other moderators in order to let them invite people.
